        <name>1.4.1.16 Simplifying algebraic fractions</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leave the expression in its most simplified form&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts_inline"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;\(\dfrac{{@numerator1@}}{{@denominator1@}}\)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;\(\dfrac{{@numerator2@}}{{@denominator2@}}\)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;\(\dfrac{{@numerator3@}}{{@denominator3@}}\)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;\(\dfrac{{@numerator4@}}{{@denominator4@}}\)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;h4 class="HELM_solution"&gt;Solution&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;[[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;[[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;[[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]] [[feedback:prt4]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;To simplify these expressions we first factorise their numerators and denominators before cancelling any common factors. Using this process we have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;\(\dfrac{{@numerator1@}}{{@denominator1@}} = \dfrac{(x-4)(x-{@a1@})}{(x-4)(x-{@a1+2@})} = \displaystyle{{@ta1@}}\)&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;\(\dfrac{{@numerator2@}}{{@denominator2@}} = \dfrac{(x-{@a2@})(x+{@a2@})}{(x-{@a2@})(x-8)} = \displaystyle{{@ta2@}}\)&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;\(\dfrac{{@numerator3@}}{{@denominator3@}} = \dfrac{(2x-3)(x-{@a3@})}{(2x-3)(x-{@a3+2@})} = \displaystyle{{@ta3@}}\)
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;\(\dfrac{{@numerator4@}}{{@denominator4@}} = \dfrac{5(z-{@a4@})}{(z-6)(z-{@a4@})} = \displaystyle{{@ta4@}}\)
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</generalfeedback>
